title: Food Healthiness Exploration
description: Scraped and cleaned data from food.com. Performed various analyses on the data: calculating recipe healthiness, testing missingness dependency, and testing recipe healthiness against its date. Created two regression models to predict recipe healthiness, trained and fitted on the dataset, with tuned hyperparameters to maximize accuracy. Created a report on the process and results, found at https://dylan-vo05.github.io/Food.com-Dataset-Exploration/

title: Bank Database Exploration
description: Cleaned and combined multiple files of bank information. Calculated dispoable income, taxable income, and loan repayment rate. Calculated and visualized various feature correlations, missingness dependency, and hypothesis tests using plotly.

title: N-Gram Language Model
description: Created a program to tokenize a training string for a language model, with capability to access a large variety of books through Project Gutenbergâ€™s API. Created a language model for token groupings of N sizes. Python model is able to generate text using conditional probability and determine the probability of an input originating from the training corpus

title: Color Identifier
description: Constructed a handheld color identifier using a Raspberry Pi, color sensor, and other parts. Able to identify 10 unique colors, tested on a wide range of swatches. Personally coded and built.

title: Store Visualization
description: Created a data visualization based on a dataset of food and healtiness data. Displayed how different supermarkets sold foods with different healthiness.

title: San Diego Bus Visualizer
description: Cleaned and processed several databases of public transit data. Created an algorithm to find the shortest path between any bus stops, visualized on a map of the county. Simulated and graphed wait times for passengers.
